*logitechmediaserver-bin-7.8.0 (08 Apr 2014)

  08 Apr 2014; Stuart Hickinbottom <stuart@hickinbottom.com>
  +logitechmediaserver-bin-7.8.0.ebuild,
  +files/logitechmediaserver-bin-7.8.0-client-playlists-gentoo.patch,
  +files/logitechmediaserver-bin-7.8.0-fix-transition-sample-rates2.patch,
  +files/logitechmediaserver-bin-7.8.0-remove-softlink-target-check.patch,
  +files/logitechmediaserver-bin-7.8.0-uuid-gentoo.patch,
  files/logitechmediaserver.init.d:
  Added ebuild for official 7.8.0 release

  13 Jan 2014; Stuart Hickinbottom <stuart@hickinbottom.com>
  files/logitechmediaserver.conf.d, files/logitechmediaserver.init.d,
  files/logitechmediaserver.service:
  Removed configuration settings for 7.8

  Removed the settings for media directory and playlist from
  /etc/conf.d/logitechmediaserver because these were not working and
  has led to some confusion.

  See /opt/logitechmediaserver/Changelog*.html following installation for
  detailed changelog.

*logitechmediaserver-bin-7.8_pre20140105 (12 Jan 2014)

  12 Jan 2014; Stuart Hickinbottom <stuart@hickinbottom.com>
  +logitechmediaserver-bin-7.8_pre20140105.ebuild,
  +files/logitechmediaserver-bin-7.8_pre20140105-client-playlists-gentoo.patch,
  +files/logitechmediaserver-bin-7.8_pre20140105-fix-transition-sample-rates2.p
  atch,
  +files/logitechmediaserver-bin-7.8_pre20140105-remove-softlink-target-check.p
  atch, +files/logitechmediaserver-bin-7.8_pre20140105-uuid-gentoo.patch,
  +files/logitechmediaserver.service, files/logitechmediaserver.conf.d:
  Added 7.8_pre20140105 ebuild

  This is a pre-release of 7.8 (which has proven very stable for
  me), built from a snapshot directly from Logitech's github
  repository. Significant changes are that Perl up to 5.16 is
  supported on x86, and up to 5.18 on amd64 (although I've only
  personally tested it with 5.16). Additionally, a systemd unit is
  installed for folks who use it.

*logitechmediaserver-bin-7.7.3 (23 Aug 2013)

  23 Aug 2013; Stuart Hickinbottom <stuart@hickinbottom.com>
  -logitechmediaserver-bin-7.7.3_alpha1.ebuild,
  +logitechmediaserver-bin-7.7.3.ebuild,
  +files/logitechmediaserver-bin-7.7.3-add-alarm-shuffle-setting.patch,
  +files/logitechmediaserver-bin-7.7.3-client-playlists-gentoo.patch,
  +files/logitechmediaserver-bin-7.7.3-fix-transition-sample-rates2.patch,
  +files/logitechmediaserver-bin-7.7.3-remove-softlink-target-check.patch,
  +files/logitechmediaserver-bin-7.7.3-uuid-gentoo.patch,
  -files/logitechmediaserver-bin-7.7.3_alpha1-client-playlists-gentoo.patch,
  -files/logitechmediaserver-bin-7.7.3_alpha1-uuid-gentoo.patch:
  Bump for official Logitech 7.7.3 release

  This release supports Perl 5.16, but only on x86. On amd64 Perl 5.14 is
  the latest supported version.

